  "doc_id": "34804",
  "text": "Evidence is accumulating that these biases have their origins in both basic biological and environmental influences. Genetic variations, such as the low expression allele of the serotonin transporter gene, are associated with emotional processing biases, which in turn mediate increased emotional vulnerability to negative life events [CITATION_1] . Traumatic experiences in adults or children can also result in negative processing biases (e.g. [CITATION_2] . In an experimental study, [CITATION_3] have further shown that attentional biases are acquired more readily in those with the low expression allele of the serotonin transporter gene. Genetic predisposition factors and learning experiences can thus interact in the acquisition of emotional processing biases.",
